---
title: Tourongo — Notification Pipeline (Real-Time + Email)
---

sequenceDiagram
    participant SVC as Any Service\n(BookingService, ReviewService...)
    participant NS as NotificationService
    participant DB as PostgreSQL\n(notifications table)
    participant WS as Spring STOMP Broker
    participant FE as Frontend React
    participant EMAIL as Brevo SMTP

    Note over SVC,EMAIL: Standard notification (in-app + email)

    SVC->>NS: createNotification(userId, type, title, message, refId, refType)
    NS->>DB: INSERT notification {userId, type, title, message, isRead=false}
    NS->>WS: SimpMessagingTemplate.convertAndSend("/topic/notifications/{userId}", payload)
    NS->>EMAIL: emailService.send() — if type is email-eligible

    WS-->>FE: STOMP frame arrives at useNotificationSocket hook
    FE->>FE: Prepend to notification list (React state)
    FE->>FE: Increment unread badge count (NotificationBell)
    FE->>FE: usePushNotifications → browser Notification API popup (if tab backgrounded + permission granted)

    Note over SVC,EMAIL: In-app-only variant (no email — avoids duplicate)
    SVC->>NS: createNotificationInAppOnly(userId, type, title, message)
    NS->>DB: INSERT notification
    NS->>WS: SimpMessagingTemplate.convertAndSend(...)
    Note over NS: No email call — used by ReviewReminderService\n(already sends richer HTML email separately)

    Note over SVC,EMAIL: 30+ Notification Types
    Note over FE: NotificationBell: click → GET /api/notifications (paginated)
    Note over FE: Mark one read: PUT /api/notifications/{id}/read
    Note over FE: Mark all read: PUT /api/notifications/read-all
    Note over FE: Unread count badge: GET /api/notifications/unread-count
